<taxonomicName id="4C044D6FFFDFF6318AEF355CFBC7FEFA" authorityName="K. Andersen" authorityYear="1910" box="[1009,1122,320,353]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Eonycteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="85" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="major">E. major</taxonomicName>
, although it is morphologically distinct based on cranial measurements and is generally recognized as a distinct species. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
